{
  "text": "Γ(x+y) is the Beta function and Γ(x) = ∞ 0 t x−1 e −t dt is the Gamma function. Note that RVQ is known to be optimal for the large n t and B tot regime with fixedB = Btot nt [CITATION_1] . We fix B tot , shown in Table I , to be the same for NTCQ and RVQ to provide a fair comparison. We also set K = 4 for θ k for NTCQ.",
